OL,3,CArmy veteran thanks organ donor's
OL,4,Cfamily for giving him 'reason to live'
OL,6,FAdrienne spent her whole life caring
OL,7,Ffor others. She was a headteacher at
OL,8,Ftwo primary schools in Bishop's Cleeve
OL,9,Fand Cheltenham before she retired.
OL,11,FEven then, she went on to build a
OL,12,Fschool in Gambia which she helped run
OL,13,Ffor another decade.
OL,15,FBut as she got older she developed a
OL,16,Fnumber of health conditions before she
OL,17,Fpassed away.
OL,19,FHer family say the act of organ
OL,20,Fdonation has been a very positive
OL,21,Fexperience.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
